› mintty renders the TUI logo made up of "block" unicode characters almost perfectly, like▐▛███▜▌, without gaps
  between glyphs, even when user chose a font that only covers some of the glyphs, or the glyphs have different
  design (less height, several pixels missing on the right, etc) from other fonts. Is there something like a smart
  fallback/font selection coercion mechanism in mintty? Please explore current code repository (mintty) and find
  out.


